feat(lib): add windows_shell_safety_stub.py minimal no-op host

v1.1.1 distribution unblocker: lib/windows_shell_safety_stub.py is a
50-line ASCII-only Python no-op that fresh users can land via the
upcoming `install.ps1 -Bootstrap` flag, fixing the "fresh clone
refuses to install" gap that made v1.1.0 a C+ for OSS distribution.

NOT pinned in lib/lead-extension.sha256 by design -- users are
expected to replace/extend with their own hardening. Gate integrity
still comes from the existing pin chain + trust anchor + marker
block. Behavior: LEAD_AGENT=1 routes through the injected marker
block to lead-pretool-hook.py (gate active); LEAD_AGENT unset hits
the fallthrough which drains stdin and exits 0.
